refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 public arrayMongoCursor::info




 This can be called before or after the query.

&reftitle.changelog;
&Version; &Description;
1.1.0
Added a number of other fields, including id (the cursor id), at (the driver's counter of which document is current), numReturned (the number returned by the server in the current batch), and server (which server the query was sent toâ€”useful in conjunction with .
1.0.10
Added started_iterating field, a boolean indicating if cursor is pre- or post-query.

  &reftitle.examples;

   MongoCursor::info example


<?php

$m = new MongoClient();
$cursor = $m->foo->bar->find(array("x" => 4), array("y" => false));
var_dump($cursor->info());

?>


